specs.title: Display latency at 60Hz should be 16.67ms (one full frame time)
Display latency at 144Hz should be 6.94ms (one full frame time)
Display latency at 240Hz should be 4.17ms (one full frame time)
Display latency at 360Hz should be 2.78ms (one full frame time)
Display latency at 480Hz should be 2.08ms (one full frame time)
Panel multiplier for IPS should be 1
Panel multiplier for TN should be 0.9
Panel multiplier for VA should be 1.3
Panel multiplier for OLED should be 0.2
BenQ Zowie XL2566K (360Hz TN) calculation matches professional testing (TFTCentral, Hardware Unboxed 2024)
ASUS ROG Swift OLED PG32UCDP (480Hz) calculation matches professional testing (Tom's Hardware 2024 - Fastest Ever Recorded)
Typical 240Hz Fast IPS calculation matches professional testing (undefined)
VA Panel with Black Smearing calculation matches professional testing (undefined)
Total lag 4.5ms should rate as EXCELLENT (<5ms)
Total lag 7ms should rate as GREAT (5-10ms)
Total lag 12ms should rate as GOOD (10-15ms)
Total lag 20ms should rate as ACCEPTABLE (15-25ms)
Total lag 30ms should rate as SLOW (>25ms)
Overdrive off should adjust response time from 5ms to ~8ms
Overdrive normal should adjust response time from 5ms to ~5ms
Overdrive extreme should adjust response time from 5ms to ~4ms
Should warn about unrealistic MPRT claims below 3ms on <240Hz monitors
Should warn about GtG spec manipulation for values <1.5ms
Should warn about extreme overdrive causing inverse ghosting
Should display temperature warning when VA panel selected
Should calculate and display refresh rate compliance percentage
Monitor with 8ms total lag should recommend: Competitive FPS, Fighting Games, Racing Sims
Monitor with 15ms total lag should recommend: MOBAs, Strategy Games, Casual Multiplayer
Monitor with 25ms total lag should recommend: Single-player Games, Turn-based Games, Casual Gaming
Should compare two monitors side-by-side
Should calculate gaming performance score (0-100)
Should complete quiz and generate recommendations
Should update visualization in real-time as FPS changes
Should display VRR range warning when FPS below 48 or 33% of refresh rate
Should explain response time vs input lag distinction
Should include manufacturer deception warnings
Should reference professional testing sources (RTings, TFTCentral, Hardware Unboxed)
Should validate response time range (0.5-20ms)
